Similar to how relationships can be specified using model string names, support the following:

```python
class User(Model):
    child = orm.relation('User')
    __dict_args__ = {'adapters': {'User': user_adapter}}
```

Currently, one must do the following:

```python
class User(Model):
    child = orm.relation('User')
    @property
    def __dict_args__(self):
        return {'adapters': {User: user_adapter}}
```

