To launch script `wait-for-elasticsearch.sh` in the ARLAS-server, this is what is required:

```bash
docker run -i -t gisaia/arlas-server:6.6.0 sh
export ARLAS_ELASTIC_NODES=elasticsearch-1:9300,elasticsearch-2:9300,elasticsearch-2:9300
first_elasticsearch_node=${ARLAS_ELASTIC_NODES%%,*}
first_elasticsearch_node_hostname=${first_elasticsearch_node%:*}
first_elasticsearch_node_port=${first_elasticsearch_node#*:}
wait-for-elasticsearch.sh $first_elasticsearch_node_hostname $first_elasticsearch_node_port
```

It would be cool if the cutting of `ARLAS_ELASTIC_NODES` was done in `wait-for-elasticsearch.sh`, so that there is no need to implement it externally.

