Flattening "Test" in the model below will run out of time/memory due to exponentially growing deepcopying it seems.

```Modelica
model A
  Real x;
end A;

model B
  A y;
end B;

model Test
  model C
    extends B;
  end C;
  C c_1;
  C c_2;
  C c_3;
  C c_4;
  C c_5;
  C c_6;
  C c_7;
  C c_8;
  C c_9;
  C c_10;
  C c_11;
  C c_12;
  C c_13;
  C c_14;
  C c_15;
  C c_16;
  C c_17;
  C c_18;
  C c_19;
  C c_20;
  C c_21;
  C c_22;
  C c_23;
  C c_24;
  C c_25;
end Test;
```

Note that:
1.  Changing all instances of `C` to `B` will flatten very fast.
2. If `B` does not instantiate `A`, but instead only contains a statement `Real x;`, flattening is also really fast.

